---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="How I Work · Rack & Roster">
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 py-12 sm:py-16">
    <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight">How I Work</h1>
    <p class="mt-5 text-xl leading-relaxed">Outside Sales Manager. One service. One price. Clean boundaries.</p>
    <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-neutral-800">
      I work with traditional strength gym owners on a monthly rhythm. The work breaks into four parts. Every engagement moves through them in roughly this order, and then cycles back as the business changes.
    </p>

    <section class="mt-11">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">The Four-Part Framework</h2>

      <div class="mt-6 space-y-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Audit</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 leading-relaxed text-neutral-800">
            I start by looking at your current state. Your CRM, your lead data, your tagging protocols, your reports. I'm looking for what's broken, what's missing, and what's lying to you. Most of what owners think they know about their numbers is wrong, and the audit is where we find out what's actually true.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Analyze</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 leading-relaxed text-neutral-800">
            I run the data properly. Lead volume by real source, not by whatever the front desk clicked. Close rates by segment. Conversion metrics at every funnel step. New memberships, active members, net change, cohort retention. Staff performance if you have a sales team. Promo ROI measured on net impact. You get a written report before every call.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Correct</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 leading-relaxed text-neutral-800">
            When the data is broken at the source, I tell you how to fix it. Source bucket logic. Tagging rules. What to capture at the point of lead entry. Report structure. You or your staff implement. I write the spec, you run it.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Coach</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 leading-relaxed text-neutral-800">
            Two calls a month, on a deliberate rhythm. Mid-month to check how we're tracking and make any in-month adjustments. End of month close-out to walk through what just happened and plan the next one. Numbers sent ahead of every call. After every call, a written summary with 3 to 5 action items, owners, and deadlines. Between calls, you can email me anytime. I respond within one business day.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">The 90-Day Cycle</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-neutral-800">
        The four-part framework runs on a deliberate schedule. Every engagement moves through three months, then cycles back.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-neutral-800">
        <strong class="font-semibold">Month 1. Baseline.</strong> I ingest your data, normalize your source tagging in my own analysis layer, and build out the full metric set for your business. You get an intake call at the start and a closeout call at the end. The closeout report is your baseline. The first time you'll have seen your real numbers, clean, and segmented the way they should be.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-neutral-800">
        <strong class="font-semibold">Month 2. Corrections.</strong> With a baseline in hand, I identify the highest-leverage fixes and bring them to the mid-month call. Target of three corrections for the cycle. Each one has a named owner on your team, a specific action, and an expected change in the data. Your team executes. I watch.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-neutral-800">
        <strong class="font-semibold">Month 3. Strategic read.</strong> Mid-month I evaluate whether the corrections actually moved the business. End of month I deliver a quarterly strategic read. The 90-day story, what worked and what didn't, patterns that aren't visible month-to-month, and a proposed focus for the next cycle. The end-of-month call is where we decide together whether to continue.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-neutral-800">
        Two calls a month. Two written reports a month. Month-to-month terms throughout. No long contracts.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">The Reports I Need to Start</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-neutral-800">
        Before we work together, I ask for three exports from your POS or CRM.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-5 space-y-4">
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-neutral-800">
          <strong class="font-semibold">12-Month Lead Report.</strong> Last twelve months of leads, with date created, source or lead type, contact info, and sale outcome.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-neutral-800">
          <strong class="font-semibold">12-Month Sales Report.</strong> Last twelve months of new membership sales, with date, member name, membership type, and price.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-neutral-800">
          <strong class="font-semibold">Membership Roster Snapshot.</strong> Current active roster plus members cancelled in the last twelve months, with join date, membership type, and cancel date where applicable.
        </p>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-5 leading-relaxed text-neutral-800">
        Don't worry about the format. Most gym databases are messy. I parsed a Manhattan strength gym from scratch in two days. Whatever your system spits out, I'll work with it, clean it up, and build the analysis around what's actually there. The parsing work is part of the service.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">What's Not in This</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-neutral-800">
        A few things I want to be upfront about, because it saves us both time.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-neutral-800">
        I don't run your ads or manage your CRM day-to-day. I don't write your sales scripts. I don't train your floor staff. I don't build software for you.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-neutral-800">
        I work with one point of contact at the gym. Usually that's the owner, but it can be a GM, Director of Sales, or whoever you designate to handle this work day-to-day. One person on the calls, one person on the email thread, one person accountable for acting on what we decide.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-neutral-800">
        What you get is a peer who's still on the floor, watching your numbers every month, telling you what the data actually says, and helping you decide what to do about it.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Before We Work Together</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-neutral-800">
        Every engagement starts with a free 2-hour data audit.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-neutral-800">
        You send me three exports from your POS ahead of the call. I do a first pass on your actual data. On the call, we walk through what's in there, I show you how each metric I'd measure tiers out against your specific setup, and I show you 2 to 3 findings I already pulled from your numbers that you haven't seen before.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-neutral-800">
        Within 48 hours, I send you a written scorecard. What your data supports, where the gaps are, and whether I'd recommend moving forward. If your data can't support the service, I'll tell you.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-neutral-800">
        This isn't a trial. It's a filter. It saves both of us from a bad engagement.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-6">
        <a href="mailto:stephen@rackandroster.com" class="underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-neutral-600">[ Book the audit &rarr; ]</a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">The Offer</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-neutral-800">$1,000 a month. Month-to-month. Structured around 90-day cycles, with a formal re-commitment conversation at the end of each.</p>
      <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-neutral-800">Maximum of three clients at a time.</p>
      <p class="mt-6">
        <a href="mailto:stephen@rackandroster.com" class="underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-neutral-600">[ Book a free data audit &rarr; ]</a>
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Base>
